# Concept registry package data is small, generated, and version-controlled
# (unlike the R2-backed source corpora above). The bare `data/` pattern
# matches this nested dir too, so re-include it explicitly.
!src/axiom_corpus/concepts/data/
!src/axiom_corpus/concepts/data/**

# legislation.gov.uk CLML source XML for the Scottish income tax ingest is
# R2-backed provenance only (README: R2 holds raw XML). It embeds upstream
# EffectId="key-..." commentary identifiers that GitHub org push protection
# false-positives as Mailgun keys; the normalized provisions carry the
# verbatim statutory text and are committed. See
# docs/ingest-runs/2026-07-05-uk-scottish-income-tax.md.
data/corpus/sources/uk/statute/2026-07-05-uk-scottish-income-tax/

# legislation.gov.uk CLML source XML for the High Income Child Benefit Charge
# (ITEPA 2003 ss.681B-681H) ingest is R2-backed provenance only, for the same
# reason: it embeds upstream EffectId="key-..." commentary identifiers that
# GitHub org push protection false-positives as Mailgun keys. The normalized
# provisions carry the verbatim statutory text and are committed; the signed
# ingest manifest records the source-XML sha256 hashes. See
# docs/ingest-runs/2026-07-05-uk-hicbc-itepa.md.
data/corpus/sources/uk/statute/2026-07-05-uk-hicbc-itepa/

# legislation.gov.uk CLML source XML for the Universal Credit minimum-income-floor
# threshold ingest (UC Regs 2013 reg 90; NMW Regs 2015 regs 4/4A) is R2-backed
# provenance only, for the same reason: it embeds upstream EffectId="key-..."
# commentary identifiers that GitHub org push protection false-positives as
# Mailgun keys. The normalized provisions carry the verbatim statutory text and
# are committed; the signed ingest manifest records the source-XML sha256 hashes.
# See docs/ingest-runs/2026-07-05-uk-uc-minimum-income-floor.md.
data/corpus/sources/uk/regulation/2026-07-05-uk-uc-minimum-income-floor/

# legislation.gov.uk CLML source XML for the UK statutory-pay / maternity ingest
# (SSCBA 1992 Part XII SMP, Part II s.35 Maternity Allowance, Part 12ZA SPP) is
# R2-backed provenance only, for the same reason: it embeds upstream
# EffectId="key-..." commentary identifiers that GitHub org push protection
# false-positives as Mailgun keys. The normalized provisions carry the verbatim
# statutory text and are committed; the signed ingest manifests record the
# source-XML sha256 hashes. See
# docs/ingest-runs/2026-07-06-uk-sscba-statutory-pay-maternity.md.
data/corpus/sources/uk/statute/2026-07-06-uk-sscba-smp/
data/corpus/sources/uk/statute/2026-07-06-uk-sscba-maternity-allowance/
data/corpus/sources/uk/statute/2026-07-06-uk-sscba-statutory-paternity-pay/
# Tax Credits Act 2002 SI rate/threshold provisions carry verbatim statutory text
# committed as normalized provisions; the CLML source snapshots trip secret
# scanners as false-positive keys, so exclude the raw sources (R2-backed).
data/corpus/sources/uk/regulation/2026-07-06-uk-tax-credits-rates/
# ESA Regs 2008 income-related applicable-amount provisions: same handling.
data/corpus/sources/uk/regulation/2026-07-06-uk-esa-income-related/

# legislation.gov.uk CLML source XML for the passported maternity/food grants
# ingest (Best Start Foods SSI 2019/193 reg. 13; Healthy Start SI 2005/3262
# reg. 8) is R2-backed provenance only, for the same reason: both embed upstream
# key-... commentary identifiers that GitHub org push protection false-positives
# as Mailgun keys. The normalized provisions carry the verbatim statutory text
# and are committed; the signed ingest manifests record the source-XML sha256
# hashes. See docs/ingest-runs/2026-07-06-uk-passported-grants.md.
data/corpus/sources/uk/regulation/2026-07-06-uk-best-start-foods-reg13/
data/corpus/sources/uk/regulation/2026-07-06-uk-healthy-start-reg8/
